title: Republican Senators Say No Boycott Planned for Jackson Committee Vote
sub_head: Supreme Court nominee on track to be confirmed next month
body:
WASHINGTON—Republican senators indicated Thursday that they don’t plan to take steps to significantly delay or block the confirmation of Supreme Court nominee Ketanji Brown Jackson, who wrapped up her testimony a day earlier and is on track for a vote early next month.
Democrats also remained hopeful that they could pick up some GOP support for her confirmation, after increasingly bitter and partisan confirmation battles in recent years.
